Queens Boulevard at the S.E. corner of Sixty-eighth Avenue (formerly Occident Street, showing in three views the George Herring residence, formerly known as 470 Queens Boulevard. The house seen in the views was owned and built by the above named individual in 1896. Views one and two show the house prior to the advance of modern New York City to this area. View No. three shows it afterwards. Some of the outbuildings seen in the views lie in Sixty-eighth Avenue (Occident Street).

April 1923
View 2: February 1924
View 3: October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
